# Server auth and roles

When auth is enabled (config has admin and/or guest credentials), the server enforces:

## Middleware (server/middleware/auth.js)

- **basicAuth** – Validates credentials; sets `req.authUsername`. No role yet.
- **createRequireAdminMiddleware(config)** – When auth is on and `adminUser` is set, only that user may proceed; others get 403.
- **createBlockGuestExceptStatsMiddleware(config)** – When auth is on and `guestUser` is set, guests may only access:
  - `/api/ping`
  - `/api/stats` (job-stats and job-stats/timeview)
  All other `/api` and `/data` routes return 403 for guests. Uses `req.baseUrl` and `req.path` (relative to mount).

## App wiring (server/app.js)

- `basicAuth` and `createBlockGuestExceptStatsMiddleware` run for both `/api` and `/data`.
- **Workflow write routes** use `createRequireAdminMiddleware`: only admin may call create, update, delete, duplicate, upload, delete file.

## Workflow write routes (admin-only)

In `server/routes/workflows.js`, `requireAdmin` is applied to:

- `PUT /workflows/:name/params`
- `POST /workflows/create`
- `POST /workflows/:name/duplicate`
- `DELETE /workflows/:name`
- `POST /workflows/:name/upload`
- `DELETE /workflows/:name/file/:filename`

When adding new write or privileged endpoints, protect them with the same admin middleware and keep guest access limited to ping and stats per the rules above.
